IX-Marine-H2-Retrofit
Copyright 2026 Bryce Lovell

This repository is an original, concept-stage engineering and systems-integration work
focused on a maritime hydrogen retrofit architecture for selected short-sea and harbor
vessel classes.

Scope of this repository includes, but is not limited to:

- protected seawater intake and treatment for electrolyzer-grade water
- onboard, berth-oriented hydrogen generation using externally supplied electrical energy
- compressed-hydrogen storage architecture
- fuel-cell and battery hybrid power integration
- safety, ventilation, shutdown, and monitoring logic
- proof-of-concept framing, bill of materials, and concept-stage assembly guidance

This repository is not presented as:
- class-approved vessel design
- certified installation package
- operational safety guarantee
- navigation, fire-response, or emergency-response substitute
- perpetual-motion or self-fueling claim from vessel drag or wave action alone

